Position oven rack one level above middle position. Preheat oven to broil. Arrange Sister Schubert Dinner Yeast Rolls, cut side up, on a baking sheet lined with aluminum foil. Top each roll with a little sauce (see Step 2). Layer each roll with turkey, tomato slices and a sprinkling of black pepper. Spoon remaining cheese sauce over each roll. Top with shredded cheddar cheese. Watching entire time, broil 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Top each with bacon slices and parsley. Serve. For the Cheddar Cheese Sauce: In a small saucepan, melt butter and whisk in flour; cook over low heat for 1 minute. Slowly add milk and continue to whisk until sauce thickens. Cook on low an additional 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove pan from heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir until all ingredients are incorporated. Return to heat, stirring for 2 minutes.